{
  "texts": [
    "F. Future Research DirectionsThe insights gleaned from this study pave the way for several promising avenues of future research in the quest for more equitable LLMs.",
    "One critical area involves exploring alternative data sources and training methodologies that minimize the propagation of biases.",
    "Investigating the impact of diverse and inclusive data sets on model fairness could offer strategies for proactively mitigating bias at the source.",
    "Additionally, the development of more sophisticated algorithms for detecting and correcting biases in real-time presents a valuable research direction.",
    "The exploration of interdisciplinary approaches, combining insights from social sciences, ethics, and computer science, could yield innovative solutions to the complex problem of bias in AI."
  ]
}